🔗🤖 Week-5 | Last Part-2 – Introduction to n8n

This document introduces **n8n**, a powerful **workflow automation platform** used to connect applications, APIs, and AI agents.

It allows you to build **automated workflows without heavy coding**.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

📌 1. What is n8n?

**n8n (Node-based automation tool)** is an open-source platform that allows you to:

✔ Automate tasks
✔ Connect different applications
✔ Trigger workflows automatically
✔ Integrate AI systems

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🧠 Simple Definition

> n8n = A tool to automate workflows by connecting apps, APIs, and services.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

📌 2. Why n8n is Important for Agentic AI

Agentic AI systems often need to:

* Send emails
* Fetch data from APIs
* Store information in databases
* Trigger external services

Instead of writing complex backend code, **n8n automates these tasks**.

Example:

```text
AI Agent → n8n Workflow → Email Notification
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

📌 3. How n8n Works

n8n uses **nodes** connected in a workflow.

```text
Trigger
   ↓
Process Data
   ↓
Call API
   ↓
Send Output
```

Each step is represented as a **node**.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

📌 4. Basic Workflow Example

Example automation:

```text
User submits form
   ↓
n8n receives data
   ↓
AI processes information
   ↓
Email sent to user
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

📌 5. n8n Architecture

```text
Trigger Node
   ↓
Processing Node
   ↓
Integration Node
   ↓
Output Node
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

📌 6. Common Nodes in n8n

| Node Type     | Purpose            |
| ------------- | ------------------ |
| Trigger       | Starts workflow    |
| HTTP Request  | Call APIs          |
| AI Node       | Use AI models      |
| Database Node | Store data         |
| Email Node    | Send notifications |
| Logic Node    | Conditions & loops |

